text.section:
The Transportation Cabinet shall promulgate administrative regulations pursuant to KRS Chapter 13A requiring the procedures for titling of all-terrain vehicles to be consistent as far as practicable with motor vehicle titling. These regulations may pertain but shall not be limited to the following:
Conditions and characteristics of certificate of title forms;
Comparison and identification of identification or serial numbers of all-terrain vehicles;
Application for title;
Processing of title applications;
Form of certificate of title;
Notation of security interests on title;
Title lien statements;
Transfer of all-terrain vehicle ownership; and
Duplicate certificate of title.
